{
  "texts": [
    "In the analysis of SM data, the sequencing depth serves as a crucial factor for understanding how it might affect the results.",
    "This impact is particularly evident when sequencing depth is insufficient, or the sample size is inadequate.",
    "A study by Li et al. (2022) reported that 15 million or higher depth as the optimal minimum sequencing to explore species level composition for metagenome-wide association studies (MWAS).",
    "The shotgun sequencing method has distinct advantages over targeted sequencing techniques, such as 16S rRNA gene sequencing.",
    "Shotgun sequencing is known for its relatively unbiased nature, making it a suitable choice for capturing the genomes of diverse species, regardless their phylogenetic origin (Lu et al., 2017)."
  ]
}